  "lyrics": "Lock Me Down Lock me down, yeah, lock me down Baby, it's a loss when I'm not around Lock me down, yeah, it's a loss when I'm not around Night came, bigger, bigger, hit it like a switch Hit it over the fence and you know you're not a fucking quitter No, lock it down, it's a loss when I'm not next to you I'm holding you down, yeah Eeny, meeny, miny, moe, I took the shit from you You know the intellect that you want to give me But now you can't see me again There's a socket on my back, my friend Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh Without me inside of the free loss zone Lost, repeat me to a different pattern of me and you I've never eaten this before I've never taken and swallowed my pride so fucking hard Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh Why you locking me away? Don't lock this feeling of fear I'll break it down and you can't even know that you've been healed Oh, you've been healed from the beginning of life Lost, looie, looie, love me I wish I could reach back and grab the light from the stars That showed me my past But somehow I know it's what's been in there always will With help, with help I can't look at any of your shame It's all deranged So don't go outside and remain calm Getting locked down, baby, getting hearts broken Coming down and when you wanna communicate You shoot yourself in the dome Nobody missed you, you're all alone Nobody missed you Rest in peace, buddy",
